
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class University {
    +String name
}

class Faculty {
    +String name
}

class Institute {
    +String name
    +String address
}

class Employee {
    +int socialSecurityNumber
    +String name
    +String email
    +static int totalEmployees
}

abstract class Staff {
}

class ResearchStaff {
    +String fieldOfResearch
}

class AdministrativeStaff {
}

class ResearchAssistant {
    +List<Institute> assignedInstitutes
    +List<Project> involvedProjects
    +List<Course> taughtCourses
}

class Project {
    +String name
    +Date startDate
    +Date endDate
    +int hours
}

class Course {
    +int id
    +String name
    +int weeklyDuration
}

class Lecturer {
}

' Define associations and relationships

University "1" *-- "many" Faculty : has
Faculty "1" *-- "many" Institute : has
Faculty "1" --> "1" Dean : headed by
Employee "1" --> "1" Dean : is a

Employee "1" --|> Staff
Staff <|-- ResearchStaff
Staff <|-- AdministrativeStaff

Employee "1" ^-- "many" ResearchAssistant : is an
ResearchAssistant "1" *-- "many" Institute : assigned to
ResearchAssistant "1" *-- "many" Project : involved in
ResearchAssistant "1" *-- "many" Course : teaches (as)

Project "1" --> "many" ResearchAssistant : involves

Course "1" *-- "1" Lecturer : is taught by (optional)

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **University** contains multiple **Faculties**.
- Each **Faculty** contains multiple **Institutes** and is led by a **Dean**, who is also an **Employee**.
- **Institute** has a known **address**.
- **Employee** is a base class with SSN, name, and email. It tracks the **total number of employees** as a static attribute.
- **Staff** is an abstract class with two types: **ResearchStaff** and **AdministrativeStaff**.
- **ResearchAssistant** is a specific type of **Employee** who:
  - Is assigned to one or more **Institutes**.
  - Can be involved in **Projects** for certain hours.
  - May also be a **Lecturer** and teach **Courses**.
- **Project** includes a name, start/end date, and number of hours.
- **Course** is uniquely identified by an ID, has a name and weekly duration.
- A **Lecturer** is used optionally to indicate when a **ResearchAssistant** is teaching.

